  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "MECHANICAL ENGINEER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Lead   the design, installation, and commissioning of process systems (e.g.,reactors,      piping networks, HVAC, utilities) and mechanical equipment for      pharmaceutical/CDMO facilities.</li><li>Oversee full project lifecycle, from technical specifications and risk assessments      to on-site installation, testing, and handover.</li><li>Ensure compliance with Singapore BCA, SCDF, HSA, and ASME standards,as well as GMP/GLP requirements.</li><li>Manage subcontractors, vendors, and cross-functional teams to deliver projects on  time and within budget</li><li>Conduct process optimization studies, troubleshoot mechanical systems, and validate installations for operational efficiency.</li><li>Enforce strict adherence to Workplace Safety and Health (WSH) Act guidelines during installation activities.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma/ Degree in Mechanical Engineering or equivalent.</li><li>1-3 years of experience in process engineering and mechanical installation in pharmaceutical, chemical, or high-precision manufacturing  sectors.</li><li>Proven  track record in managing large-scale mechanical/process installations (e.g., cleanrooms, utility systems, process automation).</li><li>Proficiency in CAD/BIM, process simulation tools (e.g., Aspen HYSYS, AutoCAD Plant 3D) and P&ID development.</li><li>In-depth knowledge of piping systems, ASME B31.3, HVAC, and pressure vessel  standards.</li><li>Strong project management, problem-solving, and client-facing communication skills.</li><li>Mandarin proficiency is advantageous for regional projects.</li></ul>",
